childs.comment: field is required to create a new object, this field can not be removed from object
childs.name: Protected

childs.comment: field does not appear in client's direct output
childs.name: ReadOnly

childs.comment: object or set stored by reference
childs.name: Unique

childs.comment: Property will be automatically set to object creation time
childs.name: AutoMTime

childs.comment: Property will be automatically update to modification time
childs.name: AutoUser

childs.comment: Property will be automatically set to current user (if available)
childs.name: Indexed

childs.comment: Create index, that allows select queries on that field
childs.name: Admin

childs.comment: Field can be accessed by administrative queries only
childs.name: ForceInclude

childs.comment: field will be internally included in all queries (useful for access control)
childs.name: ForceExclude

childs.comment: field will be excluded, if not requested directly
childs.name: Composed

childs.comment: propagate modification events from objects in that field (for object and set fields)
childs.name: Compressed

childs.comment: Try to compress data field with lz-hc (incompatible with pg-cbor)
childs.name: Enum

childs.comment: Value is enumeration with fixed (or low-distributed) number of values (enables more effective index in MDB)
childs.name: PatternIndexed

childs.comment: Create index, that allows select queries with textual patterns (also enables normal index)
childs.name: TrigramIndexed

childs.comment: Text search normalization: divides the rank by 1 + the logarithm of the document length
childs.name: TsNormalize_DocLength

childs.comment: Text search normalization: divides the rank by the document length
childs.name: TsNormalize_UniqueWordsCount

childs.comment: Text search normalization: divides the rank by the number of unique words in document
childs.name: TsNormalize_UniqueWordsCountLog
